SIMPLE: pitapat
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pitapat
<hw>Pit"a*pat`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[An onomatopoetic
reduplication of <ets>pat</ets> a light, quick blow.]</ety> <def>In a
flutter; with palpitation or quick succession of beats.</def>
<au>Lowell.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧The fox's heart went <xex>pitapat</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>L'Estrange.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pitapat</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pitapat
<hw>Pit"a*pat`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A light, repeated sound; a
pattering, as of the rain.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>pitapat</xex> of a
pretty foot.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pitch</ent>⟦br⟧
